      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since the function `open_system_backends` returns when `get_info` fails, and a NULL backend results in an error if `get_info` succeeds, a backend being NULL here ensures us that `get_info` failed and that the previous backend was the last one.\nIf the `return` in `open_system_backends` was to be replaced by a `continue`, then a `continue` would be required here.",
      "parentUuid": "72ab7c72_771334ad",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 22,
