      "writtenOn": "2026-06-16T07:11:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My original intent is that if we don\u0027t get those info, it\u0027s most likely because the backend we use cannot handle those info (mpi_file for instance). So IMO we shouldn\u0027t simply treat it as an error and still ensure a sort of baseline service for those backends.\n\nOn another note, we should probably do a \"continue\" here instead, and have the error message also state the URI that we failed to retrieve the info from. Since we can have multiple URIs into one command, one may not have the mountpoint/command backend, but others may.",
      "parentUuid": "7c8863e5_a796e60d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 64,
        "startChar": 12,
